{"id":665,"date":"2020-09-02T15:27:38","date_gmt":"2020-09-02T15:27:38","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/?p=665"},"modified":"2020-09-02T15:27:38","modified_gmt":"2020-09-02T15:27:38","slug":"livestream-update-02-09-20","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/2020\/09\/02\/livestream-update-02-09-20\/","title":{"rendered":"Livestream Update (02\/09\/20)"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><strong><em>Titans!<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Dawn of Titans team will not be able to bring you our scheduled Livestream whilst we work from home during this period. We will instead get all upcoming event and Titan information to you through our blog every Wednesday.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>But fear not &#8211; Matt, Dom and Haig will return, and we want to assure you that Dawn of Titans and the whole development team will continue working hard, running all events, releasing updates, and generally keeping the game awesome!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please note that the <strong>information below is not final<\/strong>, and certain aspects may be <strong>subject to change<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>CONTENTS<\/strong>:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Upcoming Schedule<\/li><li>Conquest Update<\/li><li>Anti-Cheating Update<\/li><li>1.39 Update<\/li><li>Alliance War &#8211; Eros <em>&#8211; <\/em>Event Details<ol><li>Titan Overview<\/li><li>The Spartans<\/li><li>Relic Overview<\/li><li>Milestone Rewards<\/li><li>Alliance Rewards<\/li><li>Chosen Titans and Boost Relic<\/li><\/ol><\/li><li>Temple Festival &#8211; The War Gods<\/li><li>DoT Content Creators<\/li><li>Unofficial Social Channels<\/li><li>Official Social Channels<br><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>UPCOMING SCHEDULE:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Conquest &#8211; <em>The Minotaur<\/em><\/strong><ul><li>STARTS: 1st September, 11:00 UTC<\/li><li>ENDS: 3rd September, 08:00 UTC<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Alliance War &#8211; <em>Eros<\/em><\/strong><ul><li>STARTS: 3rd September, 14:00 UTC<\/li><li>ENDS: 7th September, 08:00 UTC<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Portal Surge<\/strong><ul><li>STARTS: 7th September, 11:00 UTC<\/li><li>ENDS: 10th September, 11:00 UTC<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Temple Festival &#8211; <em>The War Gods<\/em><\/strong><ul><li>STARTS: 7th September, 11:00 UTC<\/li><li>ENDS: 10th September, 11:00 UTC<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Relic Festival &#8211; <em>The War Gods\u2019 Relics<\/em><\/strong><ul><li>STARTS: 8th September, 11:00 UTC<\/li><li>ENDS: 10th September, 11:00 UTC<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Alliance War &#8211; <\/strong><strong><em>Hero of the Myrmidons<\/em><\/strong><ul><li>STARTS: 10th September, 14:00 UTC<\/li><li>ENDS: 14th September, 08:00 UTC<br><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>CONQUEST UPDATE<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We are aware of a number of issues with the current Conquest event, and have released a fix that should prevent a selection of Titans from achieving unintentionally high scores in Conquest battles. In addition, we have heard your feedback, and will be returning the battle drops to those found in the Hades Conquest for the next event (we will be removing 1* drops for the next Conquest event). Thank you for submitting these issues to our support teams, and look out for a free bundle going live in the game before the end of the week to thank you for your patience and feedback.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We also want to apologize for not having our Bi-Weekly Q&amp;A post go live last week, but please do continue to get your questions in for us, and we will get an extra-large, bumper-edition Q&amp;A post live on 11th September.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>ANTI-CHEATING UPDATE<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Recently we investigated a specific hack which various long-standing DoT players and content creators alluded to in a number of livestream discussions and Q&amp;A submissions. We were able to identify and ban hundreds of cheater accounts early on in the Crothos event as a direct result of this. Repeatedly duplicating any item, or collecting rewards without legitimately earning the required Souls, will result in a permanent ban. Every account meeting either of these criteria will be identified and reviewed during all upcoming events.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We are continuing to expand the scope of our anomaly detection and automated banning that covers Gems, Divine Gems, Boost Relics, Souls, Tokens, 5* Relics, Divine Titans &amp; Titan Prestige. For obvious reasons, providing detail on these is counterproductive, but we look into all fair play issues and have a zero-tolerance policy for hackers and cheaters in Dawn of Titans.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In light of the recent issues, we want to emphasise that unintentionally benefitting from a bug or glitch is <em>not<\/em> used as a ban criterion. Examples include the recent Conquest score bug and \u2018RSS\u2019 food\/gold resource glitch. However, repeated use of exploits that require abnormal player behaviour to achieve (e.g. setting a device to Airplane Mode mid-game) will get flagged by our system, and will be manually reviewed by the team, possibly resulting in a permanent ban.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Finally, we want to thank the community again for bringing these issues to our attention, and the continued discussion around cheating from within the Discord channel, the Line chats, YouTube content comments section, and our own Customer Support and Q&amp;A channels.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1.39 UPDATE<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We are fast-approaching the release of our next update &#8211; 1.39.0 &#8211; and we wanted to share with you some details before next week\u2019s full 1.39 update blog post.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For this update, the team put a lot of focus into the early Castle Levels and new player experience &#8211; we have improved rewards, revamped and shortened the tutorials, and significantly reduced the cost and time for upgrading buildings, troops and spells at these lower levels. We want players to reach a strong competitive position earlier, so a number of other small changes have been made to ensure this.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In 1.39, a new monthly-rolling login calendar will be available, with better rewards, and a new <em>All Element Titan Token. <\/em>This token can be redeemed at the ALL ELEMENT TITAN altar from within the Temple. This altar guarantees a 4* Titan with each use (please note: all new players, and those returning to Dawn of Titans after a significant hiatus, will be presented with different calendars).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We heard your feedback and have removed the troops, spells and gold as rewards, as we are aware this can cause an unwanted build up of unclaimed rewards in the Treasure Room. Where possible, we have replaced these with Tokens, Shards and XP Potions of higher value. As with all changes in our new releases, we want to hear your feedback, so please post to our social channels and write in with your questions using the \u2018Submit your Questions\u2019 button on this site.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https:\/\/lh4.googleusercontent.com\/ud2CTUz0yMr9MwSGTllwt-dJGjWeE586V08jnjyDEC-kq3elI4vTtQMPLWe7z_L1HjYGjKOEHO3NHUFV6KO2X2aYDQTjx8WJuJT4zu4DV1agf_KaH1zOWzD7Qph9GGM_RF0igNZb\" alt=\"\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition, we\u2019ve added a number of new collections to the Titan Pantheon with all-new prizes for completing them (prizes will be revealed in the 1.39 update blog post). The collections we\u2019ve added are:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Greeks II<\/li><li>Egyptians I<\/li><li>War Gods I<\/li><li>Community Titans I<\/li><li>Winter Titans I<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Look out for our 1.39 Update blog post coming sometime in the next two weeks for more information.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"\/>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>ALLIANCE WAR &#8211; <\/strong><strong><em>Eros <\/em><\/strong><strong>&#8211; EVENT DETAILS:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https:\/\/lh4.googleusercontent.com\/CexuNiYutzJqeCBQ1UBwi5U2W0Yoyg2VVHlgBygYPtiNQJ66inq7B-B68QGa2pN0V1r-vL3k2PUsphwj7K1ZUnZtwOCksMmxeOvFVT_Nq3CLmZXxDedU17Z18dQz2zxAy6gssgH-\" alt=\"\"\/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Love is in the air this <strong>Thursday 3rd September<\/strong>, when Eros the <strong>Physical Ranger<\/strong> returns to the battlefield with his unique Rage ability.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"738\" height=\"320\" src=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/ErosSkills.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-666\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/ErosSkills.png 738w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/ErosSkills-300x130.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 738px) 100vw, 738px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Eros arrives with his <strong>signature Relics<\/strong>, alongside other rare four stars:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"696\" height=\"373\" src=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/ErosRelics.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-667\" srcset=\"https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/ErosRelics.png 696w, https:\/\/blog-dawnoftitans.github.io\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/09\/ErosRelics-300x161.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 696px) 100vw, 696px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>The <strong>Milestone Rewards<\/strong> are as follows:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"https:\/\/lh4.googleusercontent.com\/tcyJsw8spQhr